<ValidityStateStepMismatch>
<summary>
The read-only <strong><c>stepMismatch</c></strong> property of a <strong><see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState"><c>ValidityState</c></see></strong> object indicates if the value of an <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input">input</see>, after having been edited by the user, does not conform to the constraints set by the element's <c>step</c> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>If the field is numeric in nature, including the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/date">input/date</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/month">input/month</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/week">input/week</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/time">input/time</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/datetime-local">input/datetime-local</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/number">input/number</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/range">input/range</see> types and the step value is not <c>any</c>, if the value don&amp;apos;t doesn&amp;apos;t conform to the constraints set by the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/step"><c>step</c></see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/min"><c>min</c></see> values, then <c>stepMismatch</c> will be true. If the remainder of the form control&amp;apos;s value less the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/min"><c>min</c></see> value, divided by the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/step"><c>step</c></see> value (which defaults to 1 if omitted) is not zero, there is a mismatch.</para><para>Given the following:</para><para>if <c>(value - min) % 2 !== 0</c>, <c>stepMismatch</c> will be true.</para><para>If true, the element matches the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:invalid">:invalid</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:out-of-range">:out-of-range</see> CSS pseudo-classes.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">Constraint validation</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Form_validation">Forms: Data form validation</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/step"><c>step</c> attribute</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ValidityState/stepMismatch"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</ValidityStateStepMismatch>
